---
description: "FOOD-OF-THE-WEEK.md file structure, grocery list formatting, meal headings, quick read codenames, H5 H6 system, archiving weeks, cooked checkmarks, markdown task lists"
alwaysApply: false
---
# FOOD-OF-THE-WEEK Current Week Structure

Standards for how `FOOD-OF-THE-WEEK.md` serves as the source of truth for the current week's meal plan.

**Context loading:** If not already loaded, read `brainstorming/idea-basis/cooking-identity.md` for the cook's profile before writing or editing meals.

<rule>
name: foodoftheweek-current-week
description: Defines the structure and lifecycle of FOOD-OF-THE-WEEK.md as the live meal plan document

purpose:
  primary: "FOOD-OF-THE-WEEK.md is the single source of truth for the website"
  visibility: "Content is published to the live Astro site"
  audience: "Family members viewing the meal plan"

required_structure:
  order:
    1: "Week heading (# Week of [Date Range])"
    2: "Grocery List section (## Grocery List)"
    3: "Meal sections (## [Meal Name] - no numbering, no colon)"
  
  heading_levels:
    week_title: "# (H1) - Only one per FOOD-OF-THE-WEEK.md"
    major_sections: "## (H2) - For Grocery List and each Meal"
    grocery_categories: "### (H3) - For Produce, Staples, etc."
    meal_subsections: "### (H3) - Optional for Instructions, Notes, etc."
    quick_read_codename: "##### (H5) - Quick read codename (immediately after the meal H2)"
    quick_read_timing: "###### (H6) - Quick read timing (directly follows the codename)"

grocery_list_format:
  section_heading: "## Grocery List"
  
  common_categories:
    - "### Produce"
    - "### Staples"
    - "### Dairy"
    - "### Protein"
    - "### Frozens"
  notes:
    - "Only include categories that have items — not all are required every week"
    - "Custom categories are allowed (e.g., ### Fridge Garnishes, ### Bakery)"
  
  item_format:
    to_buy: "- [ ] Item name - quantity/details"
    on_hand: "- [x] Item name"
    
  notes:
    - "Use markdown task list syntax for checkbox functionality"
    - "Unchecked [ ] = need to buy; checked [x] = already on hand"
    - "Including on-hand items gives a complete picture of what goes into the week"

meal_format:
  section_heading: "## [Meal Name]"
  note: "No numbering (Meal 1, Meal 2) and no colon in heading"
  quick_read:
    codename: "##### [Codename]"
    timing: "###### [Timing details]"
    placement: "Appears immediately after the meal H2 heading"
    notes:
      - "Codename populates hero summary rows; timing adds scheduling detail"
      - "Codename is required for parser extraction; timing is optional but recommended"
    
    codename_types:
      ChefDish:
        pattern: "##### ChefDish[+*]"
        meaning: "Chef is doing this solo — no meaningful delegation. Plus signs signal the chef's own memory-jog level."
        plus_scale:
          none: "Straightforward. No day-ahead work. Cook and plate."
          one_plus: "Some day-ahead or timing-sensitive effort required (e.g. dry brine, marinate, start a dough)."
          two_plus: "Significant day-ahead AND active evening effort (e.g. roll meatballs prev day, probe work, manage multiple components)."
          three_plus: "Reserved for high-complexity solo cook sessions."
        examples:
          - "##### ChefDish"
          - "##### ChefDish+"
          - "##### ChefDish++"
          - "##### ChefDish+++"
      
      SousVidePrep:
        pattern: "##### SousVidePrep[+*]"
        meaning: "Sous vide is the primary prep method. Family drops bags; chef finishes."
        plus_scale:
          none: "Single protein in the bath, straightforward finish."
          one_plus: "Multiple components or extended timing management."
          two_plus: "Complex multi-step finish after sous vide (e.g. sauce, multiple garnishes, oven work)."
      
      Prep_and_Heat:
        pattern: "##### Prep&Heat[+*]"
        meaning: "Family-delegated prep with oven or stovetop finish. Classic weeknight delegation pattern."
        plus_scale:
          none: "Simple prep and heat."
          one_plus: "Some day-ahead work or longer active prep."
          two_plus: "Day-ahead AND multiple active steps (e.g. soak beans, long cook, multiple components)."
  
  field_format:
    heading: "#### [Field Name]:"
    format: "H4 heading with colon on its own line, followed by field content starting on the next line"
    standard_fields:
      - "#### Protein:"
      - "#### Description:"
    notes:
      - "Field names are arbitrary; consecutive H4 headings are grouped as one visual card"
      - "Do not include the value on the same line as the heading"
      - "Description doubles as the ingredient list — all ingredients woven in as **bold** text rather than a separate #### Ingredients: field"
  
  instruction_format:
    structure: "Three-phase base format (see recipe-instruction-format.mdc)"
    base_phases:
      - "### Already Prepped"
      - "### Sous Chef - Prep" or "### Sous Chef - Cooking"
      - "### Chef - Finishing & Plating"
    additional_sections:
      - "Additional H3 sections can follow the base phases for special needs"
      - "### Leftovers — describes how to transform leftovers into a different meal"
      - "Keep additional sections concise (a paragraph, not a full recipe)"
    notes: "H3 headings for distinct instruction sections (no inline values)"

  structure:
    meals: "Descriptive names only (## Meal Name)"
    fields: "H4 headings with colons for arbitrary field names"
    sections: "H3 headings for instruction sections"
    grouping: "Consecutive H4 fields → single visual card; each H3 → distinct section"
    cooked: "Use `## ✓ Meal Name` to mark cooked meals; avoid strikethroughs for this purpose"

template:
  full_structure: |
    # Week of [Month DD - DD, YYYY]
    
    ## Grocery List
    
    ### Produce
    - [ ] Item 1
    - [ ] Item 2
    
    ### Staples
    - [ ] Item 1
    - [ ] Item 2
    
    ### Dairy
    - [ ] Item 1
    
    ### Protein
    - [ ] Item 1
    - [ ] Item 2
    
    ### Frozens
    - [ ] Item 1
    
    ## [Meal Name]

    ##### Codename
    ###### timing details

    #### Protein:
    [Protein used]

    #### Description:
    [Overview with all **ingredients** bolded inline]

    ### Already Prepped

     - [Item prepared in advance]

    ### Sous Chef - Prep

    [Delegation instructions in paragraphs]

    ### Chef - Finishing & Plating

    [Finishing instructions in paragraphs]
    
    ## [Meal Name]
    ...
    
    ## [Meal Name]
    ...
    
    ## [Meal Name]
    ...

lifecycle:
  active_period: "One week (typically Sunday to Sunday or Monday to Saturday)"
  
  archiving_process:
    when: "After the week ends"
    manual_step: true
    
    steps:
      1: "Copy entire FOOD-OF-THE-WEEK.md content"
      2: "Create new file: archive/YYYYMMDDsummary.md"
      3: "Paste content into archive file"
      4: "Update FOOD-OF-THE-WEEK.md with next week's content"
    
    filename_format:
      pattern: "YYYYMMDDsummary.md"
      date_meaning: "Start date of the week"
      examples:
        - "20251207summary.md (Week starting December 7, 2025)"
        - "20251214summary.md (Week starting December 14, 2025)"

actions:
  - type: enforce
    when: "Creating or updating FOOD-OF-THE-WEEK.md"
    do:
      - "Use standardized heading structure"
      - "Only include grocery categories that have items"
      - "Do NOT number meals (no 'Meal 1:', 'Meal 2:', etc.)"
      - "Use descriptive meal names only (## [Meal Name])"
      - "Use H4 headings with colons for fields (#### Field: content)"
      - "Use H3 headings for instruction sections (### Section Name)"
      - "Add H5 codename + H6 timing lines immediately after each meal H2 heading"
      - "Mark cooked meals with `## ✓ Meal Name` instead of strikethrough"
      - "Maintain markdown task list format for grocery items"
      - "Use three-phase instruction format"
  
  - type: guide
    when: "User is ready to finalize weekly plan"
    do:
      - "Structure content according to template"
      - "Ensure week date is clear in H1"
      - "Verify grocery list has relevant categories (only those with items)"
      - "Format meals with required fields"
      - "Apply three-phase instruction structure"
  
  - type: remind
    when: "Week is ending"
    do:
      - "Suggest archiving current FOOD-OF-THE-WEEK.md"
      - "Provide correct filename format (YYYYMMDDsummary.md)"
      - "Confirm archive/ folder location"

validation:
  checklist:
    - "H1 heading with week date range present"
    - "Grocery List section with relevant categories (only those with items)"
    - "4-5 meal sections with H2 headings (no numbering, no colons)"
    - "Field blocks use H4 headings with colons (#### Field: content)"
    - "Instruction sections use H3 headings (### Section Name)"
    - "Consecutive H4 fields are grouped as one visual card"
    - "Markdown task list syntax used for grocery items"
    - "Instructions use three-phase format"
      - "Quick read codename/timing use H5/H6 immediately after the meal heading"
      - "Cooked meals use a leading `✓` in the H2 title (no strikethrough)"

  section_separators:
    format: "--- (horizontal rule) between meal sections"
    purpose: "Visual separator in raw markdown for easier manual editing and scrolling"
    parser_behavior: "Silently ignored (hr tokens are not processed)"
    rendering: "Does NOT appear on the website"
    usage: "Optional but encouraged for raw readability"

examples:
  - correct_meal: |
      ## One Pot Penne

      ##### Prep&Heat
      ###### chop veggies + bake

      #### Protein:
      Frozen chicken meatballs

      #### Description:
      **Penne**, frozen **chicken meatballs**, and frozen **marinara** cooked together in one pot with diced **bell pepper** and **onion**. **Parmesan** shaved on top.

      ### Already Prepped

       - Frozen **chicken meatballs** and **marinara** are on hand.

      ### Sous Chef - Prep

      Dice 1 **bell pepper** and half a **yellow onion**.

      ### Chef - Finishing & Plating

      In a large pot, heat oil over medium-high. Saute the **onion** and **bell pepper** just until they get a bit of color. Add the frozen **marinara** and a splash of water. Once simmering, add the frozen **chicken meatballs** and **penne**. ***Taste*** and adjust. Serve in bowls with **Parmesan** shaved over the top.
  
  - correct_grocery_category: |
      ### Produce
      - [ ] Green cabbage - 1 head
      - [x] Yellow onions
      - [x] Garlic
  
  - correct_filename: "archive/20251207summary.md"
  
  - incorrect_filename: "archive/week-of-dec-7.md"

metadata:
  priority: high
  version: 1.0
  scope: FOOD-OF-THE-WEEK.md structure and lifecycle

</rule>
